PC GP2 01 sham - C - maintained at 37-38 deg

Percussion (2021-03-01)

  • Pig: 35.2 kg

Sham:
- 13:55 - Attached percussion line to adaptor. Fill with room temperature saline.
Let it stand for 10 min.
- 14:05 - Remove percussion tube, capped adaptor.

Cooling

Started at 14:07 pm.
Brain temperature was 37 deg. Cooling was not functioning properly.
Rectal temperature was at 39.4 (entire time).
Brain temperature was between 37 - 38.5 deg.

Study ended at 12:00 pm (next day - 22h post CTP).

Cooling set up

1st target = -10.5 deg (VT output air)
Flow rate = 60 LPM
2nd target = 34.5 deg (brain temp to cool down to)
Maintenance time = 960 min once brain reached 34.5 deg
3rd target temperature = 38.5 deg (rewarm target)
Rewarm rate = 0.25 deg/h

Cooling notes

The chiller was not working. For the first 15-20 minutes when turned on, it was able to output air at around 12-13oC to the VT tube. However, after that short time, the temperature continually increased and after 9 h of operation the input air temperature to the VT was 18.5 deg and the VT output air temp was -3.7 deg. Possibly there was a leak so that we are losing Freon. Another clue to this was that the compressor was not that hot, it was measuring only 50 deg, it used to be > 70 deg. After 19h 20 min, the chiller output 19.7 deg air to the VT tube and the VT tube output air at -2.9 deg. In the lab testing the prior day by Marcus, with room temperature air, the VT tube should output -7 deg air. At 10:28 am disconnect the chiller and connected the hospital air directly to the VT. The input air to VT measured 23.2 deg.
